text.section:
The Governor shall transfer to the Authority for the Intercounty Connector:
From the Transportation Trust Fund, at least $30,000,000 each year for fiscal years 2007 through 2010;
From the General Fund or general obligation bonds, an aggregate appropriation by fiscal year 2014 equal to $264,913,000, as follows:
$53,000,000 for fiscal year 2007;
$55,000,000 for fiscal year 2010;
At least $80,000,000 for fiscal year 2011; and
The remaining balance for fiscal year 2012, fiscal year 2013, or fiscal year 2014; and
At least $10,000,000 federal aid from any source in amounts as deemed prudent.

section.section:
The report required under this subsection shall include:
An update on the progress of the project and a comparison of the actual progress to the project schedule provided to the committees in January 2005;
The revised estimate of the total project cost of the project and a statement of the reasons for any cost savings or cost overruns, relative to the estimate of $2,447,000,000 provided to the committees in January 2005;
A description of any changes to the financing plan for the project, including the impact of cost savings or cost overruns, and, consistent with the intent of the General Assembly to limit the overall amount of debt used for financing the Intercounty Connector, the specific identification of sources of funds that may be applied to address any cost overruns;
Planned expenditures by year, categorized by planning and engineering, right-of-way acquisitions, and construction;
Funding sources by year, categorized by:
Grant Anticipation Revenue Vehicle bond issuances;
Transfers from the Transportation Trust Fund;
Transfers from the General Fund;
Federal funds;
Authority cash reserves;
Authority revenue bond issuances;
Draws on a loan or line of credit extended to the State under the federal Transportation Infrastructure Finance and Innovation Act;
Bond anticipation notes; and
Any other revenue source;
A schedule of debt service for the Grant Anticipation Revenue Vehicle bond issuances and Authority revenue bond issuances; and
Financing assumptions, including maturities of bond issuances and forecasted interest rates.
